  "market_context": "YM daily chart showing Monday forming the low of the week with equal lows and a fair value gap above as the missing key level. Despite an imperfect Monday opposing run, Tuesday produced a reversal candle establishing the high of the week.",
  "key_observation": "Tuesday formed a candle two closure sweeping highs, but the hourly change in state of delivery did not occur immediately — confirmation was delayed until later in the same day when price closed through the up-close candle series.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified that Monday's profile was missing a key level — instead of a clean opposing run, price made equal lows with a fair value gap above.",
    "Noted Tuesday produced a candle two closure (sweep and close back inside) and marked it as a potential weekly high.",
    "Looked for hourly change in state of delivery on Tuesday to confirm the reversal — observed it was not immediate.",
    "Tracked the day's progression: price opened, made the high, then later closed through the up-close candle series, delivering the delayed CSD confirmation.",
    "Anticipated a protected swing high, retracement back into range forming another protected swing, and continued lower delivery for the rest of the day.",
    "Confirmed continuation as Wednesday closed below Tuesday's low, supporting further downside on Thursday.",
    "Observed Thursday expansion completed two days lower but no major objective hit, suggesting Friday could either be avoided or used for further continuation (noted as choppy).",
    "Concluded that although this was not a classic expansion (Monday formed the actual weekly low), Tuesday still formed the high of the week and the continuation profile worked."
  ],
  "outcome": "Wednesday and Thursday delivered expansion lower as anticipated; Friday was choppy with no clean objective reached.",
  "lessons": "Weekly profiles do not always match templates perfectly. The goal is to identify the high or low of the week (via candle two closure and CSD) and trade continuations in the following days — not to force-fit every week into a classic expansion template.",
